:{{see|lynx}}

==English==
===Etymology 1===
Named by the [[astronomer]] Johannes Hevelius in 1687. From {{L.}} ''[[lynx]]'', a "lynx"

====Proper noun====
{{wikipedia|Lynx (constellation)}}
'''Lynx'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[spring]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to be so faint that one needs the eyes of a [[lynx]] to see it. It lies north of the constellation [[Cancer]].

